respec - RSpec Convenience Wrapper

[1mUsage:[0m
  respec [COMMAND]
  respec [COMMAND] --help | -h
  respec --version | -v

[1mCommands:[0m
  [32mall[0m           Run full specs (default)
  [32mfocus[0m         Run specs tagged with :focus
  [32monly[0m          Run specs on files matching a pattern
  [32mexcept[0m        Run specs and exclude files matching a pattern
  [32mlast[0m          Run specs on files modified in the last N minutes
  [32mfails[0m         Run the last failed specs
  [32mcontinue[0m      Continue from where the last run stopped
  [32mrefactor[0m      Shortcut for 'respec last 2 --watch'
  [32mreset[0m         Delete the status file
  [32mcompletions[0m   Echo completions function

[1mOptions:[0m
  --help, -h
    Show this help

  --version, -v
    Show version number

[1mEnvironment Variables:[0m
  RESPEC_STATUS_FILE
    Where to store the rspec status file
    Default: spec/status.txt

  RESPEC_HELPER_PATH
    The location of the spec_helper.rb file
    Default: spec/spec_helper.rb
